{
  "text": "The rear springs and dampers are designed for larger operating loads. Bumpstops are located on the end of the damper and provide an additional damping force in the shocks. They are engaged only after a certain amount of displacement occurs between the piston and cylinder of the shock absorber. Spring, damper and bumpstop parameters can be found in [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
